<paragraph blockId="12.[264,1323,1233,1419]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Facial gibbosity small, with distinct outline. The genus is closely allied to 
<taxonomicName box="[1149,1271,1233,1258]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Machimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1149,1271,1233,1258]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Machimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the one South Korean species shares the slightly excised and thickened male sternite 
<number box="[1301,1318,1273,1299]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="8.0">8</number>
. The gonostylus is distinctly slender (
<figureCitation box="[706,797,1313,1339]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 25" captionStartId="26.[264,370,1739,1760]" captionTargetBox="[389,1178,294,1726]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[361,1245,294,1735]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 25. Male gonopods, lateral views. 13. Aneomochtherus sinensis. 14. Asilella londti. 15. Astochia virgatipes. 16. Eutolmus brevistylus. 17. Eutolmus koreanus. 18. Machimus aurulentus. 19. Machimus cf. pastshenkoae. 20. Mercuriana ussuriensis. 21. Neoitamus angusticornis. 22. Neoitamus castaneipennis. 23. Neoitamus cothurnatus univittatus. 24. Neoitamus zouhari. 25. Philonicus albiceps. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/171902/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Fig. 
<number box="[764,797,1313,1339]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="20.0">20</number>
</figureCitation>
), and the aedeagus truncated (
<figureCitation box="[1161,1309,1313,1339]" captionStart="FIGURES 26 – 48" captionStartId="27.[264,370,1636,1657]" captionTargetBox="[453,1179,326,1605]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[401,1351,326,1628]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 26 – 48. Male aedeagi, lateral and dorsal views. 26 – 27. Aneomochtherus sinensis lateral &amp; apex. 28 – 29. Asilella londti lateral &amp; apex. 30 – 31. Astochia virgatipes lateral &amp; apex. 32 – 33. Eutolmus brevistylus lateral &amp; apex. 34 – 35. Machimus aurulentus lateral &amp; apex. 36 – 37. Machimus cf. pastshenkoae lateral &amp; apex. 38 – 39. Mercuriana ussuriensis lateral &amp; apex. 40 – 41. Neoitamus angusticornis lateral &amp; dorsal. 42 – 43. Neoitamus castaneipennis lateral &amp; dorsal. 44. Neoitamus cothurnatus univittatus lateral. 45 – 46. Neoitamus zouhari lateral &amp; dorsal. 47 – 48. Philonicus albiceps lateral &amp; apex." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/171903/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Figs. 
<number box="[1230,1309,1313,1339]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="38.39">38, 39</number>
</figureCitation>
). Ovipositor similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[524,646,1353,1378]" class="Insecta" family="Asilidae" genus="Machimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[524,646,1353,1378]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Machimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but the cercus is elongated, almost as long as tergite 
<number box="[1308,1323,1353,1379]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="9.0">9</number>
(
<figureCitation box="[273,360,1393,1419]" captionStart="FIGURES 58 – 66" captionStartId="29.[264,370,1489,1510]" captionTargetBox="[442,1195,324,1416]" captionTargetId="figure@29.[378,1436,324,1452]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 58 – 66. Female external genitalia, lateral views. 58. Aneomochtherus sinensis. 59. Asilella londti. 60. Astochia virgatipes. 61. Eutolmus brevistylus. 62. Machimus aurulentus. 63. Machimus cf. pastshenkoae. 64. Mercuriana ussuriensis. 65. Neoitamus angusticornis. 66. Philonicus albiceps." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/171905/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
Fig. 
<number box="[327,360,1393,1419]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" value="64.0">64</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
